how to create your own command. suppose you wanna create a command name begh which is cat /flag.
step 1: create a directory for your command
  mkdir ~/mybin
step 2: create the begh script
  echo '#!/bin/bash
  cat /flag' > ~/mybin/begh
step 3: make it executable
  chmod +x ~/mybin/begh
step 4: Put your directory first in a path
  export PATH=~/mybin:$PATH
step 5: run command
